column1: On 1 October 2019, how many countries will be on Russia's food embargo list?
column5: ['0', 'Between 1 and 31, inclusive', 'Between 32 and 35, inclusive', '36', '37 or more']
column6: ['Non-US Politics']
column11: Russia embargoed food imports from the United States, EU member states, Canada, Australia, and Norway in August 2014 as retaliation for Western sanctions imposed after Russia's annexation of Crimea (European Commission). Iceland, Albania, Montenegro, Liechtenstein, and Ukraine were later added to the list (Yahoo). The embargo on these 37 countries was last extended through 31 December 2018 (Radio Free Europe). Since 2014, certain products have been exempted from the embargo (USDA Foreign Agricultural Services), but the list of covered countries has only expanded.

In September 2018, the improvement in the attitude of the inhabitants of Russia to Western countries, which we celebrated in the spring of 2018, ceased. Since 2017, the “ratio index” values ​​for the United States or the EU, for Ukraine, ranged from 60 to 100 points, while in the period 2014-2016 they varied from 40 to 80. The higher the index value, the favorable attitude towards the country. But, even with the growth of positive attitudes in this period, in the Russian public opinion, beginning in the winter of 2014, negative perceptions of Western countries prevailed (as the sum of answers “mostly bad” and “very bad”). The positive attitude of Russians towards China remains unchanged. https://www.levada.ru/2018/10/16/otnoshenie-k-stranam-2/
